LIFE PATTERN TRACKER – USER MANUAL

Note: This file is plain text with a .docx extension so you can open it in Microsoft Word and re-save it as a proper Word document. Replace all screenshot placeholders with your actual screenshots.

------------------------------------------------------------
1. INTRODUCTION
------------------------------------------------------------

1.1 Purpose of this manual
This User Manual explains how to use the Life Pattern Tracker system, including:
- The mobile application (for regular users)
- The web-based admin dashboard (for administrators)

It provides step-by-step instructions for all key features, with clearly marked places where you should insert screenshots.

1.2 Target users
- Regular user (mobile app):
  - Tracks daily screen time
  - Monitors habits (sleep, exercise, water, mood, etc.)
  - Views insights, scores, and recommendations
- Administrator (web dashboard):
  - Manages users
  - Reviews aggregated usage and habit data
  - Monitors system health and support requests

1.3 System overview
Life Pattern Tracker is a habit and digital wellbeing assistant. The mobile app runs on Android and:
- Reads app usage statistics (Screen Time permission required)
- Lets you log and track habits
- Provides AI-generated insights based on your behavior
- Sends gentle notifications when daily app limits are exceeded

The admin web dashboard runs in the browser and connects to the server API. It:
- Shows overall system statistics
- Allows administrators to view users (or anonymised summaries, depending on configuration)
- Provides basic management tools for support and monitoring

